.TH ANEDEXT 1

.SH NAME

Anedext \- It's an editor for text.

.SH SYNOPSYS

~$ ./anedext [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION

The Anedext text editor is an editor for text, orignally written by Calm1403.

You've two modes, normal and insert; insert is similar to Vim's replace mode, allowing a user to overwrite a file's contents, in addition to resizing the file if the user wishes to enter
more than what's already there. Normal mode is the default mode; to switch to insert, you press the key sequence CTRL+i, and to exit insert, you press ESC.

ESC is also the key you press to exit the editor.

Normal mode is also very similar to Vim's, in that it's used primarly for navigation; to move right, you press 'l,' with left, you press 'h.'

You can also save your file editing by pressing the key sequence CTRL+s.

.SH OPTIONS

There aren't any options per-se; you supply a file name as an argument to the program on execution.

.SH SEE ALSO

\%vim(1)
